SPIKE OUTCOME (tk-ad9ebd8b983f) — DESIGN CORRECTION REQUIRED before this task starts:

The original `workspaceAndWarpAvailable` design (probe GET /experimental/workspace → 2xx) is INSUFFICIENT. OpenCode's workspace HTTP endpoints are unconditionally mounted, but the internal sync machinery is gated on the `experimentalWorkspaces` runtime flag. Without the flag:
- POST /experimental/workspace hangs 5s then returns HTTP 400 with empty body
- Bad UX, no actionable error

Per user decision (option A): keep behavior as opt-in via env var; do NOT auto-mutate process.env from the plugin.

ADDITIONAL EXPORT REQUIRED in workspace-warp.ts:

```ts
export function warpFlagEnabled(): boolean {
  return process.env.OPENCODE_EXPERIMENTAL === "true"
      || process.env.OPENCODE_EXPERIMENTAL_WORKSPACES === "true";
}
```

CORRECTED workspaceAndWarpAvailable:

```ts
export async function workspaceAndWarpAvailable(deps: WarpDeps): Promise<boolean> {
  if (!warpFlagEnabled()) return false; // short-circuit: no HTTP call when flag off
  try {
    const url = new URL("/experimental/workspace", deps.serverUrl);
    const res = await (deps.fetchImpl ?? fetch)(url);
    return res.ok;
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}
```

